HEADWORD: Storekeeper
<hw>Store"keep`er</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>A
man in charge of stores or goods of any kind; <as>as, a naval
<ex>storekeeper</ex></as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>One who keeps a ⟦ldquo⟧store;⟦rdquo⟧ a shopkeeper.
See 1st <er>Store</er>, 3.</def> <mark>[U. S.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Storer</ent>⟦br⟧
